<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1797,2004]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,251]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1869,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wingpan 
<quantity box="[439,563,1869,1893]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="13.0">13–15 mm</quantity>
. Forewing light brown, broad with rounded costa; medial area black -brown; hindwing black -brown. Male genitalia with prominent 
<number box="[786,800,1908,1932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
th segment tergal and sternal plates; tegumen, vinculum, and saccus narrow; valvae broadest sub-basally; ampullae asymmetrical; digitus finger-like; phallus strongly coiled, apical end of ductus ejaculatorius with plate-like process. Female genitalia with prominently displaced ostium on left side; antrum heavily sclerotised, matching shape of phallus; membranous part of ductus bursae narrow; corpus bursae globular, with cross-shaped signum. The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[929,1085,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Micronoctuidae" genus="Mimachrostia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[929,1085,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Mimachrostia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of the subfamily Parachrostiinae, and contains four species, all with a prominent 
<number box="[867,881,226,250]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" value="8.0">8</number>
th segment tergal and sternal plates.
</paragraph>
