<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Bionomics.</emphasis>
The biotope is dominated by many herbaceous plants and shrubs, close to a brook. The single specimen was collected at light in mid September. In other regions the species is known to occur in two generations. The early stages are unknown.
</paragraph>
